cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.Distributed, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses parallel execution of smart contracts on multicore and cluster architectures. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the serial semantics of contract programming languages and proposes a new way to execute contracts in parallel. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper discusses the execution and verification of smart contracts on the blockchain. 
- cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the execution of smart contracts in a distributed system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new technique for executing and verifying smart contracts.
